{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"0808bae1-c25d-4c14-b9e9-363b32f8de4b","content":"Here's the correct attribute for each framework:\n\n| Framework | Attribute |\n|-----------|-----------|\n| **MSTest** | `[Ignore(\"reason\")]` |\n| **xUnit** | `[Fact(Skip = \"reason\")]` |\n| **NUnit** | `[Ignore(\"reason\")]` |\n| **TUnit** | `[Skip(\"reason\")]` |\n\n**Examples:**\n\n```csharp\n// MSTest\n[TestMethod]\n[Ignore(\"Blocked by issue #123\")]\npublic void MyMsTest() { }\n\n// xUnit\n[Fact(Skip = \"Blocked by issue #123\")]\npublic void MyXunitTest() { }\n\n// NUnit\n[Test]\n[Ignore(\"Blocked by issue #123\")]\npublic void MyNunitTest() { }\n\n// TUnit\n[Test]\n[Skip(\"Blocked by issue #123\")]\npublic void MyTunitTest() { }\n```\n\n> **Note:** For xUnit `[Theory]` tests, use `[Theory(Skip = \"reason\")]` — the `Skip` property is on the test attribute itself, not a separate attribute.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"23186dd7-c588-4093-ada5-cbc6423a51e4","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about test-skipping attributes across four .NET test frameworks. This is a knowledge question — no tools needed.","outputTokens":308,"requestId":"7692:32B38:1C8F9:225A6:69F2AC88"},"id":"971713d2-5652-43db-ab06-ef78d013f793","timestamp":"2026-04-30T01:12:47.230Z","parentId":"5f2bc493-dd79-49ff-9633-4aedee516930"}
